data.description: OPEN HOUSE SATURDAY MARCH 2  >>>>>>>>>>>  Welcome to your dream resort living retreat at 138 Sugar Loaf Lane. This stunning, three-bedroom, two-bathroom retirement living property offers many modern features and amenities, all nestled within a picturesque .25-acre lot.  Upon arrival, you are greeted by an impressive double-door entrance with elegant glass inlay, leading to a sophisticated foyer with tray ceilings and beautiful wood-look tile floors. This seamless flooring carries throughout all the open living areas, providing warmth and continuity.   The versatile Indigo floorplan offers a range of layout choices for the living and dining areas, perfectly complemented by a cozy gas fireplace. A split bedroom plan features carpeted floors (new carpet color is grey) in the two additional bedrooms, with one offering a closet and a guest bathroom conveniently located in the hallway.  The heart of the home lies in the spacious kitchen, which boasts a pantry, ample cabinet space, granite counters, and electric slide in range. Additional cabinets and hard surface countertops extend into the breakfast area, providing a light-filled space for meal prep and dining.  The owner's suite offers a tray ceiling, two large walk-in closets, new grey carpet with upgraded padding, and plenty of windows all overlooking the serene, wooded views. The en-suite bathroom features a luxurious soaking tub, separate shower, double sinks, and a large vanity.  Step out onto the covered back porch and relax in the peaceful surroundings of the lush trees and tranquil nature sounds. With a gas hook-up for your grill and a small patio area, the manageable yard size allows for more time spent poolside, enjoying the community's many amenities.  The laundry room provides ample storage, a utility sink, and access to the 2-car garage. Upgrades include new tile flooring, carpeting and upgraded padding, paint, HVAC, hurricane shutters, termite bait system, additional kitchen cabinets and a second pantry, handsfree kitchen faucet, keyless entry for the garage and front door, and a solar tube added to the garage for extra lighting. Fences are not allowed.  Seasons is an Active Adult, age-restricted community. The monthly HOA fee covers internet, trash pick-up, lawn care, irrigation of yards and flower beds, fitness center, indoor pool, outdoor pool, Jacuzzi, BBQ area, gated entry, and Grand Clubhouse with an onsite Lifestyle Director. In addition to all of this, you have access to Wilderness Park located behind Seasons which features (2) outdoor pools, pickle ball courts, bocce ball, basketball, and walking trails and has gated access. Don't miss your chance to make this beautiful resort living home your own! You are buying a lifestyle, not just a home!”  FLOOD ZONE X - INSURANCE IS "NOT" REQUIRED.
